description: This header file declares external API functions related to a Daemon Engine TCP object in the ANSC (Advanced Networking Service Container) framework. It provides function prototypes for creating, initializing, registering, and removing the daemon engine TCP object, along with associated object management functions.

methods.name: AnscCreateDaemonEngineTcp
methods.description: Creates and initializes a Daemon Engine TCP object with given context handles.

methods.name: AnscDetoCreate
methods.description: Creates an instance of the Daemon Engine TCP object.

methods.name: AnscDetoRemove
methods.description: Removes and frees the Daemon Engine TCP object.

methods.name: AnscDetoEnrollObjects
methods.description: Enrolls or registers necessary internal objects for the Daemon Engine TCP object.

methods.name: AnscDetoInitialize
methods.description: Initializes the Daemon Engine TCP object after creation.
